Editor's note: If you have trouble viewing the above video please click here.JOHANNESBURG - The ministers of Police and State Security will provide details on Friday afternoon of the plan to ensure safety at OR Tambo International Airport.Police Minister Fikile Mbalula visited the airport two weeks ago following brazen robberies there and reports of hijackings of passengers after leaving the airport.Plans that have already been put in place include reshuffling of police officers and security staff based at the airport.eNCA